    "id": "ontologies--core-ai-functions"
  }, "Ontologies & core 'ai' functions"), mdx("p", null, "The core ai functions are intended to be provided by the WebizenAgent. \xA0The WebizenAgent is intended to be a 'local' agent that is installed on a device that is intended to be a local webizen host server. \xA0This host implementation is also intended to be the basis for producing the installable package that is installed on a device that is intended to be a local webizen host server. \xA0This is in-turn intended to support the installation of additional packages that will have a range of different types. \xA0Some may be trained AI models, others may be applications or services or other forms of extensions."), mdx("p", null, "So, in summary, whilst the webizen agent itself is not intended to be a singular AI 'training model' or package that does everything; rather, that it is intended to be the core process that is able to be extended via additional packages that can be loaded into either or both; the device and/or the network; and/or via a federated community of webizen who pool their resources to provide support for a specified group of users who wouldn't otherwise be able to access software based tools that perform similar things in a similar way.... \xA0 What is required within the webizen agent, is the means to provide the core tools needed to preserve 'freedom of thought', which is thought to at least include a vocabulary model and the systems that are required to support the safety protocols."), mdx("p", null, "This core package / service - somewhat like an updated dictionary; is thereby intended to also support the core ontologies, and in-turn become the basis for the development of the core AI functions that are required to support the WebizenRWW. \xA0It is entirely likely that there will be more components that are required."), mdx("h3", {
